      "type": "ApplicabilityConstraint",
      "name": "Applicability constraint — tibial tray geometry and patient population",
      "description": "Model applicability is constrained to symmetric tibial tray geometries with plateau width 68–82 mm and A-P dimension 44–54 mm, for patients with BMI ≤ 40 kg/m² and gait loading profiles within ±20% of ISO 14243-1 standard cycle. Asymmetric implants, revision TKR configurations, and high-tibial osteotomy cases are explicitly excluded from this COU."
    },
