      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "rationale": "Primary QoI is peak von Mises contact stress in the UHMWPE insert, directly linked to wear mechanism (delamination and creep) documented in retrieval analysis literature. Secondary QoI is contact area, which governs stress distribution. Both QoIs are directly measurable experimentally (pressure film, digital image correlation) and are the quantities used in the regulatory acceptance criterion (CSI < 1.15). Relevance mapping to clinical endpoint documented in the evidence dossier.",
