    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors have been assessed at MRL 3. Every factor achieves its required level: seven factors require Level 3 and achieve Level 3; two factors require Level 2 and achieve Level 3 (exceeding the threshold). The validation evidence demonstrates MAPE of 8.3% against bench-top pressure film measurements (threshold 15%) and Spearman rank correlation ρ=0.94 for wear outcome prediction. Sensitivity analysis confirms peak axial load is the dominant uncertainty driver (S1=0.62) and that material property uncertainty contributes a secondary but bounded effect (±18% on peak stress). Discretization error is bounded at GCI=0.4% on the production mesh. The operating envelope is fully characterized and the applicability constraint is explicitly documented. No factor shortfalls exist; no offset rationale is required. The model is accepted for use in identifying worst-case contact stress conditions for the Class II tibial tray COU.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
